[[File:Miremad-1.jpg|thumb|150px|A chalipa by [[Mir Emad]]]] '''Chalipa''' ({{lang-fa|چلیپا|chalīpā|translation=cross|rtl=yes}}) is a panel in the [[Nastaliq]] script. There are two important panels in the Nastaliq [[calligraphy]]: ''Chalipa'' and ''Siah Mashgh''. Chalipa consists of four [[diagonal]] [[hemistich]]es of a [[poem]], which has clearly a moral, ethic and poetic theme.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.encyclopaediaislamica.com/madkhal2.php?sid%3D5549 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-10-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101122053425/http://encyclopaediaislamica.com/madkhal2.php?sid=5549 |archivedate=2010-11-22 |df= }}</ref>
