{{Infobox journal | title = Digital Scholarship in the Humanities | editor = [http://www.edwardvanhoutte.org/en/index.htm Edward Vanhoutte] | discipline = [[Digital Humanities]] | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1986–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = https://academic.oup.com/dsh | link1 = | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | cover = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0268-1145 | eISSN = 1477-4615 }} '''''Digital Scholarship in the Humanities''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] of the [[European Association for Digital Humanities]] that covers all aspects of computing and information technology applied to Arts and Humanities research. It is the main journal in the field of [[Digital humanities|Digital Humanities]]. The journal is published by [[Oxford University Press]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oxfordjournals.org/our_journals/litlin/about.html|title=About the Journal|work=Literary & Linguistic Computing|accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref> The journal was formerly known as ''Literary and Linguistic Computing'', but was renamed to emphasise a broadening in its subject focus beyond literary studies.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Literary & Linguistic Computing Overview | work = Oxford University Press | accessdate = 2016-05-28 | url = https://global.oup.com/academic/product/literary-and-linguistic-computing-14774615?cc=us&lang=en&}}</ref>
